The original RoBERTa model architecture and pre-trained weights are the work
of Facebook AI Research (now Meta AI), published in:

  Liu, Y., Ott, M., Goyal, N., Du, J., Joshi, M., Chen, D., Levy, O., Lewis, M.,
  Zettlemoyer, L., & Stoyanov, V. (2019). RoBERTa: A Robustly Optimized BERT
  Pretraining Approach. arXiv preprint arXiv:1907.11692.
  https://arxiv.org/abs/1907.11692

The MNLI fine-tune (`FacebookAI/roberta-large-mnli`) is published by Facebook
AI Research at https://huggingface.co/FacebookAI/roberta-large-mnli under the
MIT license (declared via the model card YAML front-matter `license: mit`).

This artifact (`bh-healthcare/roberta-large-mnli-int8-onnx`) is an ONNX export
of `FacebookAI/roberta-large-mnli` with INT8 dynamic quantization applied via
the `onnxruntime.quantization.quantize_dynamic` tool with per-channel scales.
The architecture, weights, and behavior are derived from and substantially
identical to the upstream source. See README.md in this repository for full
provenance.

